                <p rend="flushleft">I <hi rend="italic">Recommendations of the Paris Conference on
                        the Peace Treaty With Italy</hi>
                    <note n="7" xml:id="d311fn7">
                        <ref target="frus1946v04#pg_889">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                            889</ref>. The locations of specific articles cited in this section are
                        indicated in the annotations to the United States Delegation Minutes of this
                        meeting, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>—<hi rend="italic">Continuation
                        of the Discussion</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Articles 3, 4, and 16</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">decided</hi> to adjourn consideration of the
                    recommendations on Articles 3, 4, and 16 until the next discussion of the draft
                    Peace Treaty <pb facs="1094" n="1070" xml:id="pg_1070"/> with Italy, which it
                    was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> would be held after the Council had discussed
                    the Paris Conference recommendations with regard to the draft Treaties with
                    Roumania, Bulgaria, Hungary, and Finland and any other points on those Treaties
                    which the Members of the Council might wish to raise.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 14</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to adopt Article 14 as it appears in the
                    Draft Treaty.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 14</hi>(<hi rend="italic">A</hi>)</p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to refer the recommendation on this Article
                    to the Deputies who should submit an agreed text for the approval of the
                    Council.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">New Article, between Articles 14 and 15 Fascist
                        Organizations</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to adopt as a basis the first part of the
                    draft text of this Article up to the words “democratic rights,” and to refer the
                    article to the Deputies to prepare a new draft connecting it with Article 30 of
                    the Armistice Agreement with Italy and to submit this draft for the approval of
                    the Council.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 25</hi>(<hi rend="italic">A</hi>)</p>
                <p>There was an exchange of views on this article.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Annex III</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed to refer Annex III to the Economic Experts for study.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Annex VII</hi> [<hi rend="italic">Parts I, II, and
                        IV</hi>]<note n="8" xml:id="d311fn8">Brackets appear in the source
                        text.</note>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to refer Annex VII, Parts I, II, and IV, to
                    the Economic Experts for study.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 64, Part D, Reparation for other Powers</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to refer Part D of Article 64, which had in
                    principle been adopted by the Council of Foreign Ministers, to the Economic
                    Experts for drafting.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">II <hi rend="italic">Recommendations of the Pans Conference on
                        the Draft Peace Treaty With Roumania</hi>
                    <note n="9" xml:id="d311fn9">
                        <ref target="frus1946v04#pg_918">Vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, pp.
                            918</ref> ff.</note>—<hi rend="italic">First Reading</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 3</hi>(<hi rend="italic">A</hi>)</p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 14</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 24, para. 4</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this paragraph was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 24, para. 8C2</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to refer the question of a definition of the
                    term “United Nations shipping” to the Economic Experts for consideration.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 24 bis</hi>
                </p>
                <pb facs="1095" n="1071" xml:id="pg_1071"/>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 26</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The Conference recommendation on this Article was <hi rend="italic">adopted</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 27</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 30, paragraphs 1c and 2</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on these paragraphs was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 30 bis</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 31</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 34</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Article 36</hi>
                </p>
                <p>After an exchange of views, a decision on this Article was <hi rend="italic">deferred</hi>.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">III <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting of the Council</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Monday, November 11, 10:30 a.m.</p>
